and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical name, from the Latin form of the Hebrew name <i>Rebekah</i>, borne by the wife of Isaac, who was the mother of Esau and Jacob (Genesis 24–27). The Hebrew root occurs in the Bible only in the vocabulary word <i>marbek</i> ‘cattle stall’, and its connection with the name is doubtful. In any case, Rebecca was Aramean, and the name probably has a source in Aramaic. It has always been common as a Jewish name; in England and elsewhere it began to be used also by Christians from the 14th century onwards and especially at the time of the Reformation, when Old Testament names became popular. It was very common among the Puritans in the 17th century, and has enjoyed a tremendous vogue in England since the latter part of the 20th century, among people of many different creeds. In Scotland this is found as an Anglicized form of Beathag ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Rebecca Dobson was born in 1210, in Scotland. She married Alexander De Watson in 1239, in York, Yorkshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died about 1281, in her hometown, at the age of 72."},"et":{"1210–about 1281":"1210–umbes 1281","1210–1281":"1210–1281","1240–1305":"1240–1305","1239":"1239","1305":"1305","about 1281":"umbes 1281","1210":"1210","1240":"1240","1281":"1281","about 1240":"umbes 1240","York, Yorkshire, England":"York, Yorkshire, England","Scotland":"Scotland","Aberdeen Scotland":"Aberdeenshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1210–about 1281":"1210–noin 1281","1210–1281":"1210–1281","1240–1305":"1240–1305","1239":"1239","1305":"1305","about 1281":"noin 1281","1210":"1210","1240":"1240","1281":"1281","about 1240":"noin 1240","York, Yorkshire, England":"York, Yorkshire, England","Scotland":"Scotland","Aberdeen Scotland":"Aberdeenshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1210–about 1281":"1210–environ 1281","1210–1281":"1210–1281","1240–1305":"1240–1305","1239":"1239","1305":"1305","about 1281":"environ 1281","1210":"1210","1240":"1240","1281":"1281